    name: 'Humpty Dumpty',
    sex: 'Male',
    description: 'Humpty Dumpty neither sat on a great wall nor had a great fall that we are aware of so a name change may be in order! He is a really friendly guy who comes right up to new folks to say hello and absolutely LOVES to have his head scratched. Like LOVES it!! The opposite can be said about petting his side or scratching his backside. That he does NOT love and will let you know with a little side eye glance that is actually pretty cute despite his intention to be \'telling you how it is\'!! He isn\'t super cuddly and doesn\'t like to be picked up. He is a tall, lean fellow with really interesting markings especially around his eyes. Like any cat he loves finding a good, sunny spot for a nap. Humpty is a really playful guy - his favorite past time is playing with wand toy and anything with catnip. He is CRAZY for catnip!! He loves playing with other cats too so he would be great in a house with a feline friend. Not sure how he feels about dogs but he has seem some in his current location and seemed very interested so he might be okay with a canine companion too. All APA! cats are fully vetted, spayed or neutered, and have updated vaccines and a microchip. Lifetime support is offered by our Cat Behavior Team. For further information or to meet Humpty Dumpty, please email adopt@austinpetsalive.org.',
