    sex: 'Male',
    description: 'Big, good looking, charming Hans Dorfler is a handsome charmer who\'s just a big softy at heart! He\'ll occasionally wrestle with his kitty roommates, though he often prefers to just watch them play. He likes attention when he initiates it. He can get overwhelmed at times by too much attention and petting, so he\'s probably not the best match for small kids and excitable dogs. He is a champion napper who will amuse you with his many \'I\'m soooo comfortable! napping positions. Hans had good litter box and scratching manners. He\'s definitely not into nail trims, though. He can be a bit vocal when it\'s time to eat. Hans Dorfler has been with us for several months now, and we know he\'d love to have his own forever home soon! He\'d do well in any relatively quiet home with people who understand cat body language for \'that\'s enough petting for now, thanks!\' He\'d probably like to have another kitty friend, too. Hans Dorfler has a temporary bit of ringworm, but a lifetime of love to give. Ringworm is a common, easily treatable skin condition! All APA! kitties with ringworm are currently adoptable with ZERO fee, a free course of medication, and unlimited support! Check out @austinpetsaliveringworm on Facebook to learn more and see the awesome kitties covered in this special; and contact us with any questions you may have. All APA! cats are fully vetted, spayed or neutered, and have updated vaccines and a microchip. Lifetime support is offered by our Cat Behavior Team. For further information or to meet Hans Dorfler, please email adopt@austinpetsalive.org.',
