    breed: 'Domestic Short Hair',
    name: 'Ginger',
    sex: 'Female',
    description: 'Mellow, Sweet, Calm Being a senior cat, Ginger would be the perfect companion cat for an older couple! She is mellow and tranquil. She might playfully bat at your pen now and then, but after that will have to take a nap. Her ideal home would be quiet and low-key. She doesn\'t need to sit in your lap, but she does appreciate being scratched and petted. When she\'s had enough, she will push your hand away. Okay, got it, Ginger! Smart girl. Previous to her stay with APA!, Ginger had been declawed. As a result of this she must remain an indoor cat. Which makes perfect sense, because what she wants is to quietly lounge around the house. She mostly ignores the other cats she has met, and we think she\'d be okay with older kids who respected her age and activity level. When she gets stressed out she may over groom herself, which is her way of saying, please lower the stress! So a home with rambunctious dogs would not be a good fit. Ginger is a dainty, little old lady with good litter manners. She is an easy cat to live with and to love. If you are looking for this kind of sweetness in your life, contact us today to arrange a meet & greet! All APA! cats are fully vetted, spayed or neutered, and have updated vaccines and a microchip. Lifetime support is offered by our Cat Behavior Team. For further information or to meet Ginger, please email adopt@austinpetsalive.org.',
