    size: 'L',
    breed: 'Domestic Short Hair',
    name: 'Ryan',
    sex: 'Male',
    description: 'Quiet, Affectionate, Handsome Ryan didn\'t get enough attention in his previous home, and he is making up for lost time! As long as you approach him properly: quietly, slowly, sitting down, allowing him to come to you. And then it is obvious that he adores affection! He will sit in your lap and \'let\' you scratch his head and chin for hours; he will be reluctant to leave your warm and snuggly lap! Ryan has all he needs to be a super-friendly, awesome companion cat - now he just needs a human companion willing to take things slowly with him. Ryan is quite dashing, too, with the cluster of gray chest hairs amidst his rich, black coat: it looks like he is all dressed up, wearing a bow tie or ascot! Ryan and his foster brother, Stormy, have been pals for a while and do well together, even though Ryan is the bossy one in their relationship (and sometimes gets jealous with sharing your affection). Ryan would do well in a home with Stormy or another mellow kitty. To learn more about Stormy - https://www.austinpetsalive.org/adopt/available-cat-details/?ID=44055 In addition to playing with Stormy, Ryan is a big fan of wand toys! He will grab the wand toy and play tug-of-war with you. He is playful, but moderately so; not crazy-playful. The best home for Ryan would be quiet/low-traffic, with Stormy or another easy-going cat buddy, and adults/young adults; little kids would likely be too chaotic for him. He is about halfway to being a TOTAL lap cat, are you ready to help him go the rest of the distance? Contact us today to meet him! All APA! cats are fully vetted, spayed or neutered, and have updated vaccines and a microchip. Lifetime support is offered by our Cat Behavior Team. For further information or to meet Ryan, please email adopt@austinpetsalive.org.',
